<dec f='master/lib/librte_ethdev/rte_ethdev.h' l='2960' type='int rte_eth_mirror_rule_set(uint16_t port_id, struct rte_eth_mirror_conf * mirror_conf, uint8_t rule_id, uint8_t on)'/>
<doc f='master/lib/librte_ethdev/rte_ethdev.h' l='2938'>/**
 * Set a traffic mirroring rule on an Ethernet device
 *
 * @param port_id
 *   The port identifier of the Ethernet device.
 * @param mirror_conf
 *   The pointer to the traffic mirroring structure describing the mirroring rule.
 *   The *rte_eth_vm_mirror_conf* structure includes the type of mirroring rule,
 *   destination pool and the value of rule if enable vlan or pool mirroring.
 *
 * @param rule_id
 *   The index of traffic mirroring rule, we support four separated rules.
 * @param on
 *   1 - Enable a mirroring rule.
 *   0 - Disable a mirroring rule.
 * @return
 *   - (0) if successful.
 *   - (-ENOTSUP) if hardware doesn&apos;t support this feature.
 *   - (-ENODEV) if *port_id* invalid.
 *   - (-EIO) if device is removed.
 *   - (-EINVAL) if the mr_conf information is not correct.
 */</doc>
